    # Phase 65 — OverrideContext Connection Teardown — Phase Summary

    ## Architectural Pivot: B-prime

    Phase 65 retired ALL long-lived extension-owned `duckdb_connection` handles from the
    `semantic_views` extension. Under B-prime, every callback that receives `ClientContext &`
    opens a fresh `Connection(*context.db)` inside a `ConnGuard` RAII wrapper for its
    catalog-read needs, and drops the guard before returning. The catalog WRITE (CREATE /
    DROP / ALTER) still rides the Phase 58 rewrite-to-native pattern onto the caller's conn
    through the binder — preserving v0.8.0 transactional DDL byte-identical.

    The path to B-prime traversed two falsified alternatives:
    - Option A (per-call duckdb_connect from sv_parser_override) failed on the parse thread (D-10, 43-of-47 sqllogictest regression).
    - Option A2 (context.Query from sv_plan_function) deadlocked on ClientContext::context_lock (`A2-DEADLOCK`).
    - Option B (per-call duckdb_connect from sv_plan_function) failed for the same C-API cached-db_handle reason (`PLAN-THREAD-RC1`).
    - Option B-prime (per-call C++ Connection(*context.db)) succeeded at every lifecycle phase tested (`PLAN-THREAD-RC0`, `READ-BIND-RC0`).

    See `65-RESEARCH.md` §16 + §17 for the full mechanism + handle audit; `65-OPTION-B-SPIKE.md`
    and `65-READ-PATH-SPIKE.md` for empirical evidence.

    ## Plans Completed

    | Plan | Wave | Outcome |
    |------|------|---------|
    | 65-01 | 1 | ConnGuard RAII + watchdog test scaffolding (B1..B4 + B11) + Wave-0 spike evidence — SHIPPED |
    | 65-02 | 1 | Reverted Plan 02 partial + added sv_register_table_function C++ helper + trampolines |
    | 65-03 | 2 | Deregistered sv_parser_override; promoted sv_parse_function + sv_plan_function; retired H1 catalog_conn |
    | 65-04 | 3 | Ported 7 read-side functions (list_*, show_*, dims, metrics, facts) to C++ Catalog API |
    | 65-05 | 3 | Ported 6 + 2 remaining read functions + scalars; retired H2 query_conn |
    | 65-06 | 4 | Retired TEMP-PLAN-04 conn; structural guard test; LIFE-04 + TECH-DEBT 25/26; just test-all GREEN |
    | 65-07 | 5 | Close-out: dead code cleanup + final regression verification (just ci) + this SUMMARY |

    ## Requirements Traceability

    | ID | Status | Evidence |
    |----|--------|----------|
    | LIFE-01 | CLOSED | B1..B4 + B11 + 4 new read-side watchdog tests all pass; in-process RW→RO returns within 5s. See 65-06-SUMMARY.md + uv run output. |
    | LIFE-02 | CLOSED | B-prime mechanism documented in 65-RESEARCH.md §16; trade-off record in §8 + §16.5. PHASE-65-GUARD structural test enforces invariant. |
    | LIFE-03 | CLOSED | test_in_process_bootstrap_then_readonly + variants in test/integration/test_readonly_load.py (Plan 01 + Plan 06). |
    | LIFE-04 | CLOSED | .planning/milestones/v0.9.0-phases/63-readonly-database-load-support/deferred-items.md updated in place (Plan 06 Task 3). |

    ## TECH-DEBT Filed

    - **TECH-DEBT 25** — cached-`duckdb_database` Phase 62 defect (naturally resolved by Phase 65 B-prime).
    - **TECH-DEBT 26** — duckdb-rs BindInfo does not expose ClientContext / duckdb_database (workaround shipped; upstream PR is the eventual resolution; likely supersedes TECH-DEBT 19).

    ## Architectural Diff (v0.9.0 → v0.9.1 Phase 65)

    | Aspect | v0.9.0 | v0.9.1 (B-prime) |
    |--------|--------|------------------|
    | catalog_conn (H1) | Long-lived, opened at LOAD, leaks Database lifetime | RETIRED; per-call C++ Connection probe in sv_plan_function |
    | query_conn (H2) | Long-lived, opened at LOAD | RETIRED; per-call C++ Connection inside SvRustBindDataWithConn for semantic_view + explain_semantic_view (query-scoped) |
    | sv_parser_override | Owned the success path; called rewrite_* with cached conn | DEREGISTERED; default parser dispatches to sv_parse_function on unrecognised prefix |
    | sv_parse_function | Error-reporting only (Phase 62 caret path) | Success-path entry: structural parse + payload stash; caret path preserved |
    | sv_plan_function | Unreachable (placeholder body) | Success-path entry: per-call C++ Connection probe + native SQL emission via Rust |
    | Read-side functions | duckdb-rs `register_table_function_with_extra_info` with shared CatalogReader (carrying H1 conn) | C++ Catalog API `CreateTableFunction` with per-call Connection in trampoline bind |
    | Scalars (get_ddl, read_yaml) | duckdb-rs `register_scalar_function_with_state` | C++ `sv_register_scalar_function` with per-call Connection in trampoline invoke |
    | OverrideContext | `{catalog: CatalogReader, is_file_backed}` — long-lived conn | `{catalog_table_present, is_file_backed}` — stateless config |
    | Transactional DDL | INSERT on caller's conn via ParserExtensionPlanResult | UNCHANGED — INSERT still rides binder onto caller's conn |
    | LIFE-01 (in-process RW→RO) | Busy-spin > 45s | Returns within 5s on every tested combination |

